<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"/>
  <title>Business & Development â€“ City of Miami</title>

  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;600;700;800;900&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">

  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/header.css">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/footer.css">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/business.css">
</head>
<body>

<%- include("partials/header") %>

<main class="business-page">

  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="business-hero">
    <h1>BUSINESS &amp; DEVELOPMENT</h1>
    <p>Resources, permits, and opportunities to grow in Miami</p>
  </section>

  <section class="business-layout">

    <!-- FILTERS -->
    <aside class="filters">
      <h3>FILTERS</h3>
      <button class="filter-btn active" data-filter="all">All</button>
      <button class="filter-btn" data-filter="startup">Start a Business</button>
      <button class="filter-btn" data-filter="permits">Permits & Licensing</button>
      <button class="filter-btn" data-filter="zoning">Zoning & Land Use</button>
      <button class="filter-btn" data-filter="incentives">Incentives</button>
      <button class="filter-btn" data-filter="construction">Construction</button>
    </aside>

    <!-- CONTENT -->
    <section class="business-grid">

      <!-- CARD -->
      <article class="business-card" data-category="startup">
        <h4>START A BUSINESS IN MIAMI</h4>
        <p>
          Miami offers a supportive ecosystem for entrepreneurs, startups, and small
          businesses. From registration to local compliance, the city provides
          step-by-step guidance to help you launch successfully.
        </p>

        <button class="read-more">READ MORE</button>

        <div class="card-more">
          <ul>
            <li>Register your business with the State of Florida</li>
            <li>Obtain a local business tax receipt</li>
            <li>Confirm zoning compliance for your location</li>
            <li>Apply for industry-specific permits if required</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="business-card" data-category="permits">
        <h4>PERMITS &amp; LICENSING</h4>
        <p>
          Most commercial activities require permits or licenses to ensure public
          safety and regulatory compliance.
        </p>

        <button class="read-more">READ MORE</button>

        <div class="card-more">
          <ul>
            <li>Business Tax Receipt (BTR)</li>
            <li>Health & safety inspections</li>
            <li>Alcohol and food service permits</li>
            <li>Temporary event permits</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="business-card" data-category="zoning">
        <h4>ZONING &amp; LAND USE</h4>
        <p>
          Zoning regulations determine how land and buildings can be used throughout
          the city.
        </p>

        <button class="read-more">READ MORE</button>

        <div class="card-more">
          <p>
            Zoning approval is required before opening, expanding, or redeveloping a
            property. Developers must comply with land use, density, and environmental
            regulations.
          </p>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="business-card" data-category="incentives">
        <h4>ECONOMIC INCENTIVES</h4>
        <p>
          The City of Miami offers financial incentives to encourage business growth
          and job creation.
        </p>

        <button class="read-more">READ MORE</button>

        <div class="card-more">
          <ul>
            <li>Tax increment financing (TIF)</li>
            <li>Workforce development grants</li>
            <li>Small business assistance programs</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="business-card" data-category="construction">
        <h4>CONSTRUCTION &amp; DEVELOPMENT</h4>
        <p>
          New construction and renovations must follow city building codes and review
          processes.
        </p>

        <button class="read-more">READ MORE</button>

        <div class="card-more">
          <ul>
            <li>Building permit applications</li>
            <li>Plan reviews and inspections</li>
            <li>Environmental impact requirements</li>
            <li>Final occupancy approval</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </article>

    </section>

  </section>

</main>

<%- include("partials/footer") %>

<script src="/js/business.js"></script>
</body>
</html>